atoms.title: Recurrence Relation
atoms.instructor_notes: Another way to see that the number of nodes is n is that the invariant at each level is that the sum (across the level) of the values is exactly n.  The first level is n.  The second one is 2 (n/2) = n.  The third is 4 (n/4) = n.  The last is some number of 1s that adds up to n.  Must be n!  -MLL

atoms.title: Tangled Hypercube
atoms.instructor_notes: Oops, that's n/2 edges added at each level because each of G1 and G2 have n/2 nodes. -MLL
